    <summary>Free open-source code editor and official successor to Adobe Brackets</summary>
    <description># Phoenix Code

Phoenix Code is a free, open-source code editor and the official successor to Adobe Brackets. It is a visual editor for websites, web apps, and Markdown with live preview that updates as you type.

## Screenshots

![Screenshot](https://cdn.statically.io/gh/Aurocosh/chocolatey-packages/master/automatic/phoenix-code/img/screenshot.png)

![Screenshot](https://cdn.statically.io/gh/Aurocosh/chocolatey-packages/master/automatic/phoenix-code/img/screenshot-2.png)

![Screenshot](https://cdn.statically.io/gh/Aurocosh/chocolatey-packages/master/automatic/phoenix-code/img/screenshot-3.png)

## Features

- Live preview for HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and Markdown
- Design Mode — edit text, images, and layout directly in the preview
- Built-in terminal and Git integration
- Smart code completion and fast project-wide search
- Extensions and themes

Phoenix Pro adds AI assistance with visual and runtime context from the rendered page.

</description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/phcode-dev/phoenix-desktop/releases/tag/prod-app-v5.1.24</releaseNotes>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency id="webview2-runtime" />
    </dependencies>
